history.content: I know Professor Sahai has been really vocal about taking EE126 before CS189 and that's why I enrolled in it, but even after getting an A in CS70, EE16A, and EE16B, I don't feel like I'm prepared. The class has been growing rapidly to what seems like around 250, but the latest grade data we have is Sp 17 when 68 people took it. Accounting for selection bias, the fact that the grade avg is still ~3.1 makes me a little hesitant about the upcoming semester (given I'm interested in the 5 yr masters so I need to have a high gpa to apply.) Would any instructors in the EECS department be willing to publish grade data for Fa 17 and Sp 18 so students can make a more informed decision about taking the class? (The early drop deadline definitely does not help.) Thank you so much.
